From 8be433d5cc1ffba694a0e1a534bf1aea029de954 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramanathan Choodamani <rchoodam@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 15 Jul 2025 22:14:15 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:DP:wifi:ath12k:Add support to extract and send rx flows
 for Mirrored SCS

When a new rx flow arrives for a peer that supports MSCS and has an
active MSCS session, the driver uses FSE to program the rule to hostapd
which then programs it to the network stack.

To ensure, the rule is programmed only once per new flow, a new metadata
tag is introduced which will be appended to the old FSE metadata.

Changes introduced:
1. Add support to parse the Rx msdu flow and get the flow_info
2. Use a new metadata tag for MSCS_RULE_PROGRAMMED and add it to the
   existing metadata tag.
3. Program the FST entry.
    a. Add a new entry with new fse metadata
                      OR
    b. Update the same entry but with new metadata.
4. Use this new metadata tag to check if re-programming required or not.
5. After parsing the flow_info derived from the MSDU sent by an MSCS peer,
   send the flow info to upper layers which will send it to user space
   eventually using NL80211 framework

Patch-dependency: 0132-0002-QSDK-wifi-ath12k-Add-helper-functions-for-calculatin.patch
Patch-work: NA
Tag: MSCS

Signed-off-by: Ramanathan Choodamani <rchoodam@qti.qualcomm.com>
